Ask HN: Which companies offer surrogacy assistance programs?
text:
I recently found that Adobe offers a Surrogacy Assistance Program[1] for employees in the U.S.

This was the first time I'd heard of such an employee benefit. I Googled around a little and this doesn't seem to be such a broadly offered employment benefit, so I'm interested to learn if a company you currently work at or have previously worked at offers something similar.

In particular, I'd be interested to learn how "employee-friendly" such programs and benefits are in practice.

[1]: https://benefits.adobe.com/document/201

Ask HN: Is scientific facts more important than scientific thinking?
text:
Scientific Fact: Up-to-date science discoveries that absolutely excludes ancient knowledge like astrology or metaphysics.

Scientific Thinking: How you think when you can't do experiment about the matter at the moment. While the seemingly like term of "scientific method" is defined to be the almost same thing but when you are doing/can do experiment at the moment.

I think knowing scientific facts is more important because people are just gathering pseudo-facts and that leads to the wrong conclusion all the time.
